    cellular: "ACT is a third-wave behavioral therapy using acceptance, mindfulness, and values-based action to increase psychological flexibility. The six core processes: cognitive defusion (separating from thoughts), acceptance (allowing experiences without avoidance), present moment awareness (mindfulness), self-as-context (observing self vs thinking self), values (clarifying what matters most), and committed action (taking steps aligned with values). Psychological inflexibility results from experiential avoidance, cognitive fusion, lack of values clarity, and inaction. ACT uses metaphors (passengers on the bus, quicksand), experiential exercises, and mindfulness practices. Research supports ACT for depression, anxiety, chronic pain, substance use, and workplace stress.",
