    cellular: "Stress management integrates psychoeducation, relaxation training, cognitive restructuring, and behavioral coping skills. The transactional model of stress (Lazarus and Folkman) describes stress as resulting from the perception that demands exceed resources. Primary appraisal evaluates threat, secondary appraisal evaluates coping resources. Coping styles: problem-focused (addressing the stressor) and emotion-focused (managing the emotional response). Relaxation techniques include progressive muscle relaxation (Jacobson), diaphragmatic breathing, guided imagery, autogenic training, and mindfulness meditation. Time management, assertiveness, and social support enhancement are behavioral components.",
